\subsection*{Hazard functions}
Comparing the three hazard functions in Fig. \ref{fig1}B, we found that the third function --- with both growth-dependent and growth-independent terms, i.e. $(\alpha e^{-\beta X_{i}} + \gamma)\delta_t$ --- significantly outperformed both the growth-independent only (i.e. null) or growth-dependent only functions (Fig. \ref{fig2}A). Moreover, we found that predictive skill was higher when using stem diameter growth over stem-area growth (Fig. \ref{fig2}A). A summary of hyper parameter estimates can be found in Table S1.

